{
  "doc_id": "18692",
  "text": "Sicca syndrome is common in systemic sclerosis (SSc) (60%), almost always due to salivary fibrosis. But SS is present in only 17 to 29% of the cases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , and a few and controversial data are available about Sjo¨gren's characteristics in patients with SSc. These controversial data on characteristics of SS associated with SSc are probably due to the lack of a consensual definition of sSS until recently. sSS is now clearly defined by criteria from the American-European consensus group (AECG) published in 2002 [CITATION_5] and thus, the characteristics of patients with SS and SSc can now be studied.",
